# Notes Demo
# A card's optional third section (question --- answer --- note) holds extra
# context — text and images — shown only after you answer, and on
# answer-visible screens (first-view reveal, flip-through). Never with an
# unanswered question.

Shallot: onion or not?
---
onion
~ not onion
---
A shallot is Allium cepa var. aggregatum: a true onion, just a small
clustering one.

Garlic: onion or not?
---
not onion
~ onion
---
Garlic is Allium sativum. Same genus, different species — close, but not an
onion.

@img images/rings.png
What does an onion look like inside?
---
rings
~ layers of seeds
~ segments
---
@img images/rings.png
Concentric rings: each ring is a leaf base wrapped around the bud. The note
can repeat the question's image — or show a different one.

Scallion: onion or not?
---
not onion
~ onion
---
@img images/scallion.png
No bulb, just stalks (pictured) — an allium, but not an onion. This note has
an image the question didn't.

# answer-mode: type
The common onion is Allium ____ (type the species)
---
cepa
---
"Cepa" is Latin for onion. It survives in English via French: cive gave us
"chives".

Chive: onion or not?
---
not onion
~ onion
